ost\nneeded. Also a law that contains a\nprovision for rehabilitating tha in\nland nun that ha may be returned\nto society as a producing unit.\"\nGive the Children a Chance\nBefore the Kentucky legislature\nat Frankfort, President Green em\nphasized the need of legislation to\nprohibit ehild labor and night work\nfor women. He also touched on the\nunemployment situation.\n\"Children should he placed in\nschools and playgrounds, not in\nfactories and mills,\u201d he declared,\n\u201cit is np to the state legislatures\nto enact laws that will protect the\nlittle ones from the greed of in\nhuman employers.\n\"It Is a vicious policy that forces\nwomen to do night work In South\nern mills. It breaks down the\nhealth of future mothers and im\npoverishes the nation.\u201d\nIn speaking of unemployment,\nMr. Green urged an extensive pro\ngram of construction by city, slate\nand federal governments.\n\"The present condition is chaos,\u201d\nhe said. **We must have a definite\nplan to tide ever periods of unem\nployment.\u201d\nPresident Green waa introduced\nto the legislators by Wood Axton\nof Louisville, one of the largest\nemployers of labor in Kentucky, j\n\"Better wages mean better busi- j\nness, and the American Federation!\nof Labor stands for both,\u201d fae told j\nthe members. I\nWASHING DESKS\nla Uw Folaakt Chancery Ceart.\n\u25a0TATI OP ARKANSAS.\nCounty of Pulaski. m.\nNora Vinton. PLaiotlff,\nTi, No 4JtW.\n9. B Vinton. Defendant.\nThe Defendant, i S. Vintcn, ta warned\nto appear In this court within thirty deya\nand onawer the complaint of the Plain\ntiff. Nor* Vlnum.\nMarch it. 1M9.\nW. I MAHOMET. Chancery ciart.\nBy Martarer Farrell. U C.\nCharter S. Barley. Solicitor for PSaJnUft\nLouta Tmrtoaratl. Attorney ad Litem.\nt-Al-24\u20144-4-11\nLACLEDE HOTEL\nNew Kutcrarat\nus Vat TOW St.\nKhm With ar Without Board\nOar Meals Caaaot Bo Surpassed\nU Costa\nBreakfast to 8\nDinner 114* to 1>M\nSooner S48 to T P. M.\nUrn. Anna M. Bn ran\nDancing Every Wednesday.\nFrid